msgid ""
"Signals give meaningful names to values buried in your submission data. "
"Instead of writing assertions against raw paths like "
"<code>p.project.compliance.targets.max_site_eui_kwh_m2</code>, you define a "
"signal called <code>target_eui</code> and write <code>s.target_eui</code> in "
"your CEL expressions."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Each signal has a <strong>name</strong> (a valid identifier like "
"<code>floor_area</code>) and a <strong>data path</strong> that points to "
"where the value lives in the submission payload. Validibot resolves the path "
"when a validation run starts and makes the value available as "
"<code>s.&lt;name&gt;</code> in every step's CEL assertions."
msgstr ""

